data.description: NICE NEW PRICE! Cozy 1925 bungalow nestled in the popular Euclid-St. Paul neighborhood. This home welcomes you with a sunlit living/dining area featuring lovely hardwood floors, crown molding, a decorative fireplace, and a convenient breakfast bar with a pass-through to the kitchen. The kitchen is equipped with stainless steel appliances, granite-tile countertops, and a laundry closet housing a stacking washer & dryer.  The primary bedroom offers a peaceful retreat with French doors leading to the yard, a walk-in closet, and an ensuite bathroom with a walk-in shower. The two additional bedrooms and a full bath are thoughtfully placed on the opposite side of the house in a split floor-plan layout. Outside, a charming fully fenced outdoor space is adorned with Florida-friendly plants, and a parking pad is available if needed.  NEW R00F IN JUNE 2020, NEW WATER HEATER IN 2023 AND NEW A/C IN 2024 PROVIDING ADDED PEACE OF MIND.  Situated in Flood Zone X, this home eliminates the need for flood insurance. Enjoy the convenience of the location, with close proximity to local restaurants to include Nitally's, Left Bank French Bistro and Hooks Sushi. Picturesque Crescent Lake Park, and Downtown St. Pete are also within walking distance. Easy access to I-275 allows for a quick drive to the nearby Gulf Coast beaches and two international airports in St. Pete/Clearwater and Tampa.
